  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6839.18 sitting just above the 6834 flip strike in PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and actively providing liquidity by selling into strength above 6840 and buying any dips toward 6835. The massive positive gamma wall at 6850 (+33.9B) creates a significant ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the 6820 negative gamma floor (-3.3B) acts as a magnet below current levels. The gex_surge event with 20.3% flow changes suggests increased option activity is reinforcing these boundaries, keeping price action range-bound between 6835-6850.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect mean-reverting chop between 6835-6850 with dealers capping upside moves.",
